Source: pg-oidc-validator
Section: database
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Ruohang Feng <rh@vonng.com>
Build-Depends: debhelper-compat (= 13), postgresql-all (>= 217~), g++ (>= 13), libcurl4-openssl-dev, libssl-dev
Standards-Version: 4.7.2
Rules-Requires-Root: no
Homepage: https://github.com/percona/pg_oidc_validator

Package: postgresql-PGVERSION-pg-oidc-validator
Architecture: any
Provides: postgresql-pg-oidc-validator
Depends: postgresql-PGVERSION, ${shlibs:Depends}, ${misc:Depends}
Description: OAuth and OIDC token validator for PostgreSQL 18
 pg_oidc_validator implements PostgreSQL 18's OAuth validator module API. It
 discovers OIDC providers, fetches and caches their JWKS data, validates JWT
 access tokens, and maps a configured token claim to the PostgreSQL identity.
